On Sat, Jun 7, 2008 at 4:58 AM, Nishant Karve <mystudygroup@...> wrote:
> Hi Experts,
> I am new to JUnit. However I have configured and written some simple use
> cases. Could anybody please tell me how can I write test case for method
> returning void, method returning iterator. Please explain me with sample
> code snipetts if possible.

Please consider reading the JUnit FAQ document. It contains many very
useful examples and techniques. For example, the there is a section
just about testing methods that have void return types. Here is a link
for you:

http://junit.sourceforge.net/doc/faq/faq.htm#tests_4

I hope this helps, but please read the whole FAQ before asking further
questions, as you will find that it answers many of the questions you
didn't even realise you were going to need to ask.

> Thanks,
> Nishant...
